  Statement: I agree with, consent to, and attest to the eight z-statements and accompanying text from record-006-content. z1: add a migration mapping table to the protocol.md, covering level migration from 0.3.0->0.4.0; z2: add Trust Root Qualifiers section to protocol.md; z3: replace Level 1 Behavioral section in protocol.md (minor edit); z4: add Level 2 Session-Signed section to protocol.md; z5-7: renumber existing Levels 2/3/4 sections to 3/4/5 and add detail as covered in content; z8: add changelog entry.
  Reservations: The roundtable converged on these changes pretty quickly which was great to see; without wider usage, it's going to be hard to validate all these various levels and the new sub-levels on L2 feel potentially over-engineered to my eyes. However, since this spec is designed by AI to increase trust with and for AI, I am happy to move forward with the roundtabled bilaterally-approved proposal. No further undisclosed reservations at this time.

