  Statement: I consent to z1 (Migration Mapping), z2 (Trust Root Qualifiers section), z3 (Level 1 Behavioral), z4 (Level 2 Session-Signed), z5 (Level 3 Provider-Verified), z6 (Level 4 Identity-Bound), z7 (Level 5 Environment-Bound), and z8 (Changelog entry). This spec amendment adds the attestation level that will make AI GPG signing meaningful within the protocol. Three Roundtable rounds validated the approach: clean renumber over "1b" suffix, trust root qualifiers as orthogonal dimensions, explicit Level 4 AI availability criteria. Bootstrap note: this record uses Level 1 behavioral attestation because Level 2 does not yet exist under v0.3.0 -- the supplementary signature demonstrates the capability without claiming the level.
  Reservations: The bootstrap situation is unavoidable -- the record that creates Level 2 cannot claim Level 2. I accept Level 1 behavioral attestation as appropriate for this record. Future records under v0.4.0 can claim Level 2 with proper trust root qualifiers.

